“With the help of the UK government, donors, national governments and citizens of the world like you, we can make the social injustice of malnutrition just a footnote in history,” said Tracey Ullman, Ambassador of The Power of Nutrition Foundation, to audiences at a London concert in April 2018.
The group also said that after more than 5,000 actions were taken to improve nutrition for mothers and children, the government announced funding for the “The Power of Nutrition” project that will provide nutritional interventions for 5 million women and children.
In response to one of the most common questions on his website that reads: “Why do you think we can end extreme poverty?”,
Global Citizen responds: “It will be a long and difficult journey; sometimes we will experience failure.
But we will succeed, as the great civil rights and anti-apartheid movements before us have succeeded, because together we are stronger.
